description: Dengue is a viral fever spread through mosquito bites. It’s common in many tropical regions across the globe, but has recently appeared in more temperate climates.
title: Dengue fever, once confined to the tropics, now threatens the U.S.

description: A judge has sentenced Tyler Wenrich to a fine and time served after he pleaded guilty to bringing ammunition into Turks and Caicos.   Wenrich is one of several American tourists recently charged.
title: Second American avoids prison on Turks & Caicos ammunition charge

description: A mass of boulders, earth and splintered trees can be seen in new drone footage of the devastation from a landslide that wiped out a village in Papua New Guinea.
title: Drone footage shows scale of destruction in Papua New Guinea landslide

description: Violence is a key issue in Mexico's upcoming elections including for Catholics still shocked by a gang's killings of priests in Cerocahui in 2022 and amid Pres. López Obrador's avoidance of confronting cartels and gangs.
title: Violence is key issue in Mexico's election, including for Catholics jolted by priest killings

description: President Cyril Ramaphosa, who has staked his reputation on cleaning up the image of the African National Congress, will lead the party into an election.
title: South Africa’s Ramaphosa steers African National Congress into pivotal election

description: Soldiers in the Kharkiv region are battling Russians forces day and night in an effort to halt their advance as Ukrainian officials say Moscow's forces are continuing to try and breach defenses.
title: Ukrainian soldiers in Kharkiv battle Russians forces day and night

description: Pope Francis used an offensive slur for gay men in a closed-door discussion with Italian bishops last week, two sources who were in the room told NBC News.
title: Pope Francis used an offensive slur during a discussion about gay men

description: A Papua New Guinea official told the United Nations that more than 2,000 people are believed to have been buried alive by a landslide as the search and rescue operation transitions to a recovery mission. NBC News’ Kelly Cobiella reports on the threats of more landslides and the challenges of getting foreign aid workers to the disaster site.
title: Threat of more landslides in Papua New Guinea loom as recovery mission continues

description: There is growing outrage over a deadly Israeli air strike in Rafah that killed dozens at a camp for displaced civilians. Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu describes it as a “tragic incident.” NBC’s Raf Sanchez reports for TODAY.
title: Netanyahu acknowledges Rafah strike as ‘tragic incident’

description: Temperatures rose to over 122 degrees in parts of Pakistan, as an ongoing heat wave gripped more areas, including the southern district of Sukkur. Authorities have urged people to stay indoors, hydrate and avoid unnecessary travel.
title: Pakistan heat waves sees temperatures soar to over 122 degrees

description: It’s safe to say it wasn’t the mid-flight entertainment they were expecting.
title: Naked on a plane: Man arrested after alleged nude aisle run forced plane to turn back

description: Palestinians fled areas of Rafah as the fighting between Israel and Hamas continued in the vicinity. Israel pounded Rafah with airstrikes and tank fire, pressing its offensive in Gaza's southern city despite international condemnation of an attack that sparked a blaze in a tent camp for the displaced, killing at least 45 people.
title: Palestinians flee areas of Rafah as fighting continues around them

description: Palestinians searching through charred remains described a “horrifying” scene of people running to escape the blaze that swept through a tent camp in Rafah, as Israeli forces pushed deeper into the southern Gaza city on Tuesday despite mounting global condemnation.
title: Israeli tanks reach central Rafah as Gazans search through charred remains of tent camp

description: Locals in northern Papua New Guinea were searching desperately for survivors with shovels and their bare hands through muddy rubble and debris. More than 2,000 people were buried in the landslide according to the local government.
title: The search for Papua New Guinea landslide victims continues as rescuers dig through mud

description: A rocket launched by North Korea to deploy the country’s second spy satellite exploded shortly after liftoff Monday, state media reported.
title: North Korean rocket carrying its 2nd spy satellite explodes shortly after launch

description: Images of Chinese warships seen off the coast of Taiwan served as a dire warning of a potential invasion that could disrupt the technology supply chain, plunge the world into an economic catastrophe, and start a hot war between the U.S. and China. NBC News’ Ken Dilanian speaks with a geopolitics expert who believes an actual invasion could be over before the U.S. even has a chance to respond.
title: Expert says a Chinese invasion of Taiwan could be over in less than an hour
